The subject focuses on the understanding and practical application of marketing strategies and brand communication in various business environments. Students learn to analyze marketing and communication problems and develop solutions that meet their needs. The course also covers various marketing tactics, such as advertising, sales promotion, public relations and social media, and teaches how to apply these tactics effectively. At the end of the course, students develop a marketing and communication strategy suitable for their idea.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to introduce the fundamentals of marketing and brand communication and to provide an overview of various strategies and tactics that can be used in the planning and implementation of marketing activities and brand communication.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: *understands the nature and importance of marketing strategies and communication in a business environment; *analyzes marketing and communication problems and solves them effectively; *creates a marketing and communication strategy suitable for their idea, presents it and implements it in their creative project.
